-- Mogadishu Fighting Kills Nine People and Wounds Another 30, Paramedic Says
-- Hamsa Omar
-- 2010-07-27T07:32:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/mogadishu-fighting-kills-nine-people-and-wounds-another-30-paramedic-says.html

          
          
             At least nine people have been
killed and 30 wounded in fighting in the Somalian capital,
Mogadishu, Ali Muse Sheikh, a paramedic at Nationlink and
Lifeline Africa medical service, said in an interview today.  
 The fighting was between government forces and Islamist
insurgents.  
 Separately the President of the semi-autonomous region of
Puntland, Abdirahman Mohamed Farole, said 13 Islamist insurgents
from the Al-Shabaab group were killed in fighting in comments
broadcast by Mogadishu-based Radio Horn Afrik.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Hamsa Omar in Mogadishu via Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        